doc.previous: The following were abbreviations during Middle and Early Modern English using the letter thorn
doc.after: Thorn in the form of a Y survives to this day in pseudo archaic uses particularly the stock prefix Ye olde The definite article spelled with Y for thorn is often jocularly or mistakenly pronounced ji or mistaken for the archaic nominative case of the second person plural pronoun ye
